A total of 15 goals were scored in the Nigerian Professional Football League (NPFL) games played on Sunday. TheCable looks at how teams fared across various venues on matchday 2 of the 2021/22 campaign. Rivers United 3-0 Katsina The Pride of Rivers recorded an emphatic 3-0 win over Katsina United in Port-Harcourt. Nasarawa 1-1 Gombe It was a 1-1 outcome between Nasarawa and Gombe at the Lafia Township Stadium. Remo Stars 3-0 Heartland FC Two goals by Andy Okpe and one from Samuel Anakwe helped Gbenga Ogunbote’s team secure all three points at stake. Rangers 0-1 Enyimba Victor Mbaoma’s 88th minute strike ensured that George Finidi’s boys ran away with maximum points in the Oriental derby. Wikki Tourists 1-0 Niger Tornadoes Abdullateef Abiola scored the only goal of the encounter. Abia Warriors 1-0 Sunshine Stars After losing to Enyimba on matchday one, Abia Warriors redeemed themselves with a 1-0 victory over Sunshine Stars. Shooting Stars 1-1 Akwa United Utibe Archibong opened the scoring for the Uyo-based side in the 29th minute but Ayo Adejubu netted an equaliser in the dearth to share the spoils at the Adamasingba Stadium, Ibadan, Oyo state. Dakkada 2-0 MFM Aniekan Ekpe Okon and Musa Bashiru’s efforts in the 44th and 83rd minutes respectively ensured that the Uyo-based side snatched all three points at stake. Plateau United 1-0 Kwara Muhammad Zulkifilu’s 5th minute strike was the difference between Plateau and Kwara in Jos. Kano Pillars 0-0 Lobi Stars It was a goalless affair between Kano Pillars and Lobi Stars at the Sani Abacha Stadium, Kano.